comments.body:
Using long column in metastore table to store max and min date is fine, but reusing {{LongColumnStatsData}} in thrift interface to return result not so much. I think we should add new thrift structure {DateColumnStatsData}} something like :
{code}
struct DateColumnStatsData {
1: optional Date minDate,
2: optional Date maxDate,
3: required i64 numNulls,
4: required i64 numDVs
}
{code}

and than metastore after retrieving # of days from backend, should compute Date, populate this struct and return results back to client.
